<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3211] Handle Connect WorkerTask shutdown before startup correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3211</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a follow-up from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3092&quot; title=&quot;Rename SinkTask.onPartitionsAssigned/onPartitionsRevoked and Clarify Contract&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-3092&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-3092&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The shortcut exit from awaitShutdown() in WorkerTask can lead to an inconsistent state if the task has not actually begun execution yet. Although the caller will believe the task has completed shutdown, nothing stops it from starting afterwards. This could happen if there is a long delay between the time a task is submitted to an Executor and the time it begins execution.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
